               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1–31v + Emmanuel)</locus>
                     <author key="person_2465074">RICHARD ROLLE</author>
                     <title key="work_4279">Latin Psalter</title>
                     <note>Fols. 1–6 contain the beginnings of Pss. 49 (f. 1v), 54 (f. 2), (Emmanuel has the beginnings of Pss. 82 and 87 on the exposed sides), 93 (f. 3), 95 (f. 3v), 99 (f. 4), 100–101 (f. 4v), 105 (f. 5r), 107 (f. 6v). The text is continuous from f. 7 ‘Hoc opus eorum’ (Ps. 108: 20), though occasionally hard to read and defective on fols. 14 and 31; ends ‘ex populo suo. Explicit compendiosa exposicio super psalterium per Richardum Heremitam de Hampole.’ </note>
                     <note>Pr. Cologne 1536; Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 7298; Allen, <title>Richard Rolle</title>, pp. 165–9.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2">
                     <locus>(fol. 32; 32v blank)</locus>
                     <author key="person_7386286">Ps.-AUGUSTINE (?REMIGIUS)</author>
                     <title key="work_7344">De Laude Psalmorum</title>
                     <incipit>Canticum psalmorum animas decorat </incipit>
                     <explicit> peccatum agere.</explicit>
                     <note>Followed by the distich ‘Ter quinquagenas cantat Dauid ordine psalmos’: <ref target="http://webserver.erwin-rauner.de/php_ancarm/ancarm_refwerke.php?opus=1000&amp;var=WIC&amp;nr_char=19209"><title>WIC</title> 19209</ref>.</note>
                     <note><title>PL</title> 131. 142B-D; Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 369, &amp;c. </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3">
                     <author key="person_2465074">RICHARD ROLLE</author>
                     <title key="work_4286">Emendatio Vitae</title>
                     <incipit><note>(Beg. impf.)</note> istarum semitarum </incipit>
                     <explicit> et graciarum accio in secula seculorum amen.</explicit>
                     <note>From Merton Coll. 58. c. 8, three leaves.</note>
                     <note>Ed. N. J. Watson (Toronto, 1995), pp. 33–68; Allen, <title>Richard Rolle</title>, pp. 230–45.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4">
                     <title type="desc">Ten things a man should try to possess in himself.</title>
                     <incipit>Notandum est ut homo possit amplius proficere </incipit>
                     <explicit> diffinire dicunt.</explicit>
                     <note>From Merton Coll. 58. c. 8, one leaf.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5">
                     <author key="person_2465074">RICHARD ROLLE</author>
