               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="Gregorian" notAfter="1400" notBefore="1375">S. XIV ex.</origDate>
                     <origPlace><country key="place_7002445">England</country></origPlace>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>Written in England, probably at the College before the Reformation, dismembered by, and probably during, the 1590s, in Oxford. </provenance>
                  <provenance>Used in binding Merton Coll. <q type="shelfmark">54. b. 12</q> (F. de Ripa, Lyons 1541), <q type="shelfmark">58. c. 4–8</q> (Bertachinus, Basel 1573), and Cambridge, Emmanuel Coll. 318. 3. 14 (the 5th vol. of M. Flacius <hi rend="italic">et al</hi>., <title>Historia Ecclesiastica</title>, Basel 1560–1574). The binder (‘C. E.’) worked for John Betts of Trinity Hall, Cambridge (d. 1599).</provenance>
                  <provenance>Additional four still in Merton Coll. <q type="shelfmark">58. c. 8</q>, and two as pastedowns in Cambridge, Emmanuel College, 318. 3. 14; thirty-eight leaves altogether. </provenance>
               </history>
